either above line 1 or below line 2, but in both cases a shorter line length and a centred text could account for this. The absence of a guide line above line 1 suggests that this may be the first line of the text; but there does seem to be the faint trace of a guide line visible below line 2, which would then be the upper guide line for a hypothetical line 3. The break at the beginning of line 2 makes it formally impossible to know if there were one or two additional letters at the start of line 2, but the nature of the surviving text makes this unlikely.",{"_":49,"ana":50,"ref":51},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":53,"dimensions":62},{"_":54,"ref":55}," The letters are neatly and precisely cut, with elegant thin serifs. A has a light cross-bar and the letters are similar to those in  and , as are the triangular interpuncts.",[56,59],{"_":57,"target":58},"ISic003572","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003572",{"_":60,"target":61},"ISic003573","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003573",[63,69,73],{"type":64,"l":65,"from":66,"to":66,"h":67,"unit":68},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","60","mm",{"type":64,"l":70,"from":71,"to":71,"h":72,"unit":68},"Line 2","line2","43",{"type":74,"l":75,"from":66,"to":71,"h":76,"unit":68},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","not measured",{"_":78,"notBefore":79,"notAfter":80,"precision":23},"1st century CE",1,100,[82,86],{"_":83,"type":84,"ref":85},"Halaesa","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225",{"_":87,"type":88,"ref":89,"offset":90},"Castel di Tusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[92],[93,94],37.99907,14.26197,{"_":96,"type":97,"geo":18},"On display in new lapidarium","observed",[99,106],{"n":100,"url":101,"height":102,"width":103,"desc":104,"surfaceType":105},"screen","ISic003574_tiled.tif","2304px","3072px","Photo J. Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina","front",{"n":100,"url":107,"height":102,"